            "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://mastodon.social/@appassionato\" class=\"u-url mention\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">@<span>appassionato</span></a></span> <br>ImageDescription: Photography of a large forest fire with a text box saying: Here\u2019s the feedback loop: global warming is driving wildfires, those fires are releasing carbon monoxide into \u2018 the atmosphere, that carbon monoxide is cannibalizing the \u2018 hydroxyl radicals that would normally oxidize methane, the methane in the atmosphere is lasting longer than before, longer lasting methane means a spike in global methane exactly as NOAA is reporting, and finally, the ~ spike in methane is increasing the heating of the planet, driving more global warming\u201d <br>ELIOT JACOBSON , PHD . <br>@EliotJacobson </p><p>Source: Is the Methane Catastrophe Happening Right Now? climatecasino.net <br>---------------------</p><p>my comment: <br>This is *one* of the feedback loops \ud83d\ude2c </p><p>However, the global warming effect of totally unnecessary fossil fuel usage is still much higher than the feedback loops. </p><p>-&gt; We can still manage to maintain a liveable world. But with every month our governments continue sith business-as-usual, the crash will be harder.</p>",
